1
00:00:56,257 --> 00:00:58,968
FILING FOR LOVE

2
00:01:04,640 --> 00:01:06,392
Is he still waiting
in the emergency room?

3
00:01:10,312 --> 00:01:12,565
No, there's no need.
I'll call you back.

4
00:01:12,940 --> 00:01:14,358
I'll just get off here.

5
00:01:14,984 --> 00:01:17,528
It's still pretty far from here.
Just past the intersection...

6
00:01:17,778 --> 00:01:19,196
In-a!

7
00:02:37,608 --> 00:02:39,485
Excuse me. Nurse?

8
00:02:39,568 --> 00:02:41,236
Doesn't he need surgery right away?

9
00:02:41,320 --> 00:02:42,655
Why is there a delay?

10
00:02:42,738 --> 00:02:44,531
Let me find out. Just a moment.

11
00:02:47,409 --> 00:02:49,161
Don't we have any available OR yet?

12
00:02:49,244 --> 00:02:51,830
They're full. The one that's left
is being prepped for a VIP.

13
00:02:51,914 --> 00:02:53,874
- Why?
- Then

14
00:02:54,166 --> 00:02:55,876
can't you organize
a transfer or a temporary OR?

15
00:02:56,460 --> 00:02:59,380
Do something!
You can't just leave him here!

16
00:03:01,215 --> 00:03:02,216
In-a.

17
00:03:03,801 --> 00:03:05,469
You can help, Jae-yeol, can't you?

18
00:03:05,552 --> 00:03:07,179
Call someone at Haemu Hospital.

19
00:03:07,262 --> 00:03:09,473
Please, I beg of you. Help him out.

20
00:03:14,728 --> 00:03:16,855
TIME IN SURGERY

21
00:03:16,939 --> 00:03:18,440
TIME IN SURGERY, ANESTHETIC DURATION
CURRENT TIME

22
00:03:32,246 --> 00:03:35,499
Out of all the trauma surgeons,
Dr. Yoon is the best.

23
00:03:35,582 --> 00:03:36,875
Don't you worry.

24
00:03:36,959 --> 00:03:38,627
I'll keep an eye on the patient, too.

25
00:03:39,336 --> 00:03:41,296
- Thank you, director.
- Bye, then.

26
00:03:49,179 --> 00:03:51,765
OPERATION ROOM

27
00:05:23,273 --> 00:05:25,609
Mr. Noh, are you awake?

28
00:05:25,692 --> 00:05:26,693
Mr. Noh.

29
00:05:54,596 --> 00:05:58,141
EPISODE 8:
DESIRE &amp; HOPE

30
00:05:58,225 --> 00:06:00,185
HAEMU GENERAL HOSPITAL

31
00:06:00,269 --> 00:06:01,645
I'm coming for you!

32
00:06:01,728 --> 00:06:03,564
- Stop!
- No!

33
00:06:05,774 --> 00:06:07,276
Catch me if you can!

34
00:06:08,777 --> 00:06:10,779
Do you think this is
some kids' playground?

35
00:06:11,196 --> 00:06:12,990
I'm a patient, okay?

36
00:06:13,657 --> 00:06:16,994
I need some peace and quiet to rest!

37
00:06:17,077 --> 00:06:19,913
Hey, we brought you
some expensive food, so eat it!

38
00:06:19,997 --> 00:06:22,374
No, thanks. I lost my appetite.
You can eat it all.

39
00:06:23,292 --> 00:06:25,669
You poor thing. You have no appetite?

40
00:06:26,336 --> 00:06:28,755
Tell me if there's anything you want.
I'll make it for you.

41
00:06:29,089 --> 00:06:30,465
By the way...

42
00:06:30,591 --> 00:06:32,426
I haven't seen that lady recently.

43
00:06:32,509 --> 00:06:34,344
The head of your department.

44
00:06:34,803 --> 00:06:35,804
You're right.

45
00:06:35,888 --> 00:06:38,640
When you were unconscious,
she came by all the time

46
00:06:38,724 --> 00:06:41,393
and wouldn't stop looking at you
with those forlorn eyes.

47
00:06:41,476 --> 00:06:43,228
I haven't seen her since you woke up.

48
00:06:44,187 --> 00:06:48,025
Do you think you'd feel better
if she were to visit?

49
00:06:48,442 --> 00:06:50,903
You woke up when she was with you.

50
00:06:50,986 --> 00:06:51,987
Hey.

51
00:06:52,362 --> 00:06:53,780
What's going on between you two?

52
00:06:54,323 --> 00:06:56,074
She didn't seem like just a coworker.

53
00:06:56,408 --> 00:06:57,701
There's more to it, isn't there?

54
00:06:59,077 --> 00:07:00,162
She's not just your boss.

55
00:07:00,245 --> 00:07:02,372
She's your sweet darling, isn't she?

56
00:07:04,833 --> 00:07:07,377
Will you stay out of my business?

57
00:07:08,503 --> 00:07:11,131
Is my little brother embarrassed?

58
00:07:11,214 --> 00:07:14,092
Oh, you cutie pie.

59
00:07:15,177 --> 00:07:16,553
What's wrong with you?

60
00:08:05,852 --> 00:08:07,062
That smells amazing.

61
00:08:18,782 --> 00:08:21,118
You treat me like
I'm your errand girl.

62
00:08:21,201 --> 00:08:23,245
Who craves a toasted sandwich
at the crack of dawn?

63
00:08:23,328 --> 00:08:24,997
It made you come to see me.

64
00:08:25,539 --> 00:08:27,124
I came by because I was afraid.

65
00:08:27,207 --> 00:08:29,376
Who sends over 20 texts
asking for a toasted sandwich?

66
00:08:29,459 --> 00:08:31,753
What were you so afraid of
when I was unconscious

67
00:08:31,837 --> 00:08:37,259
that made you look after me
around the clock for days?

68
00:08:39,594 --> 00:08:40,846
My sisters told me all about it.

69
00:08:41,888 --> 00:08:43,974
They said they were moved to tears.

70
00:08:47,352 --> 00:08:48,353
I was afraid.

71
00:08:51,481 --> 00:08:52,566
It was scary.

72
00:08:55,152 --> 00:08:56,361
And also...

73
00:08:57,237 --> 00:08:59,573
As your superior,
I should look out for you.

74
00:08:59,656 --> 00:09:00,949
I was just checking in

75
00:09:01,033 --> 00:09:02,200
to see if you were dead or alive.

76
00:09:14,671 --> 00:09:18,383
Sure, I bet you were just looking out
for an employee.

77
00:09:19,342 --> 00:09:21,053
But since you're looking out
for me anyway

78
00:09:22,262 --> 00:09:24,222
could you get me discharged
and take me home?

79
00:09:25,891 --> 00:09:27,893
- You're asking me to do that?
- Yes.

80
00:09:34,399 --> 00:09:37,152
Handle that box with care.

81
00:09:37,235 --> 00:09:38,945
There are quite a few breakables.

82
00:09:39,362 --> 00:09:42,199
Why is there so much luggage
when you were stuck in a ward?

83
00:09:42,866 --> 00:09:45,494
They deliver all sorts of things
to hospitals these days.

84
00:09:50,332 --> 00:09:52,167
What am I even doing here?

85
00:09:53,752 --> 00:09:56,379
Why should I get you discharged
and take you home, too?

86
00:09:56,755 --> 00:09:58,673
I still have stitches in my stomach

87
00:09:58,757 --> 00:10:01,259
and I have so much stuff
with no one else to help.

88
00:10:01,760 --> 00:10:04,262
Isn't this the least you can do
for your staff?

89
00:10:07,099 --> 00:10:08,225
Wait and see.

90
00:10:08,308 --> 00:10:09,684
As soon as those stitches come out

91
00:10:09,768 --> 00:10:13,146
I'll make you work extra hard
to make up for the time you wasted.

92
00:10:13,647 --> 00:10:14,689
Sure.

93
00:10:15,190 --> 00:10:16,733
That's the truth.

94
00:10:17,109 --> 00:10:19,694
That area is very undervalued.

95
00:10:20,112 --> 00:10:22,197
You think redevelopment is old news

96
00:10:22,280 --> 00:10:23,782
but land always retains its value.

97
00:10:24,199 --> 00:10:25,408
It does.

98
00:10:26,284 --> 00:10:28,662
Do something!
You can't just leave him here!

99
00:10:28,912 --> 00:10:31,289
Please, I beg of you. Help him out.

100
00:10:35,001 --> 00:10:36,211
Don't you agree, Jae-yeol?

101
00:10:38,255 --> 00:10:40,298
- I'm not sure.
- Goodness...

102
00:10:40,966 --> 00:10:43,593
He never gets the timing right.

103
00:10:43,885 --> 00:10:47,013
You seem to be against the idea
of turning that place upside-down.

104
00:10:47,848 --> 00:10:50,851
A lot of people would lose
their homes and livelihoods.

105
00:10:51,017 --> 00:10:52,352
They get compensated for that.

106
00:10:52,644 --> 00:10:54,062
We don't kick them out penniless.

107
00:10:54,563 --> 00:10:57,691
My brother is so softhearted.

108
00:10:58,275 --> 00:11:01,236
He could never turn a blind eye
to people in need since he was young.

109
00:11:01,319 --> 00:11:03,947
He always makes a sacrifice
or gives up what's his.

110
00:11:04,406 --> 00:11:06,867
The Jeons are known to be ruthless.
You know what my father's like.

111
00:11:06,950 --> 00:11:08,618
He's the most ruthless businessman
in the country.

112
00:11:11,454 --> 00:11:14,291
I just don't get
who Jae-yeol takes after.

113
00:11:14,374 --> 00:11:15,500
What I do know

114
00:11:15,959 --> 00:11:17,502
is that he's not like our father.

115
00:11:19,421 --> 00:11:20,881
He must be like his mom.

116
00:11:41,902 --> 00:11:43,862
Sorry. I apologize instead.

117
00:11:43,945 --> 00:11:45,238
He had too much to drink.

118
00:11:47,157 --> 00:11:49,451
I contacted the PR Team. Get his car.

119
00:11:49,534 --> 00:11:50,911
I'll bring the VP downstairs now.

120
00:12:04,466 --> 00:12:05,842
Hello, A-jeong.

121
00:12:06,593 --> 00:12:08,011
Why are you acting out of character?

122
00:12:10,222 --> 00:12:12,933
You can't lash out like this
when a board meeting's coming up.

123
00:12:14,851 --> 00:12:16,436
Will you let me off today?

124
00:12:25,570 --> 00:12:26,655
Joo In-a...

125
00:12:27,906 --> 00:12:30,283
What on earth is she to you?

126
00:12:33,119 --> 00:12:35,330
She's someone I would die with.

127
00:12:43,088 --> 00:12:45,924
How could you not keep an umbrella
in your car for emergencies?

128
00:12:47,175 --> 00:12:50,053
I should get one for you
for next time.

129
00:12:53,390 --> 00:12:55,976
If A-jeong's home,
why don't you ask her to bring one?

130
00:12:56,893 --> 00:12:58,520
Why should we bother her?

131
00:12:59,437 --> 00:13:01,648
It's a passing shower.
I'll wait until it stops raining.

132
00:13:07,112 --> 00:13:08,905
Why did you and A-jeong break up?

133
00:13:10,156 --> 00:13:11,574
I don't exactly know why.

134
00:13:11,658 --> 00:13:13,451
She ghosted me out of the blue.

135
00:13:14,035 --> 00:13:15,578
Didn't you ask her why?

136
00:13:15,662 --> 00:13:16,830
You must've seen her at work.

137
00:13:17,497 --> 00:13:18,540
I didn't ask.

138
00:13:19,874 --> 00:13:21,626
I assumed there was a reason
she didn't tell me.

139
00:13:26,881 --> 00:13:27,924
Why do you ask?

140
00:13:28,717 --> 00:13:31,886
Would you have asked
if you were in my place?

141
00:13:34,597 --> 00:13:35,765
If that had been me...

142
00:13:36,850 --> 00:13:38,351
If I were A-jeong

143
00:13:40,687 --> 00:13:42,147
I would have wanted you to ask.

144
00:13:45,734 --> 00:13:48,361
Oddly enough, I have a habit

145
00:13:48,653 --> 00:13:50,322
of hiding the truth
when it matters most.

146
00:13:51,781 --> 00:13:53,283
While on the inside

147
00:13:54,576 --> 00:13:56,578
I hope someone
would drag the truth out of me.

148
00:13:57,662 --> 00:13:59,831
I hope someone
wouldn't give up on me.

149
00:14:00,832 --> 00:14:03,043
I get selfish and contradictory.

150
00:14:06,671 --> 00:14:10,008
Wouldn't it be easier
just to be honest?

151
00:14:14,179 --> 00:14:15,347
Do you mean that?

152
00:14:15,889 --> 00:14:17,015
So what?

153
00:14:17,349 --> 00:14:19,934
- You want me to get married?
- Yes, I mean it.

154
00:14:20,143 --> 00:14:22,562
Should we elope or something?

155
00:14:23,021 --> 00:14:24,939
And get disowned and lose everything?

156
00:14:26,149 --> 00:14:28,735
- I don't want that kind of life.
- In-a.

157
00:14:28,818 --> 00:14:29,986
Either way

158
00:14:30,528 --> 00:14:32,864
I was never naive enough
to think what we had

159
00:14:33,907 --> 00:14:35,325
would last forever.

160
00:14:36,034 --> 00:14:38,703
You can get married freely.
There's no need to feel guilty.

161
00:14:39,204 --> 00:14:40,413
I really am

162
00:14:41,331 --> 00:14:42,540
okay with it.

163
00:14:49,881 --> 00:14:54,010
I think it's because
I don't know how to be happy.

164
00:14:58,807 --> 00:15:01,684
Just when I think I'm happy,
I feel uneasy and anxious.

165
00:15:02,268 --> 00:15:03,937
I ask myself,
"Do I even deserve this?"

166
00:15:05,271 --> 00:15:06,439
I get afraid.

167
00:15:06,815 --> 00:15:08,316
I hide and run away.

168
00:15:10,110 --> 00:15:11,986
I'm just more used to being unhappy.

169
00:15:19,494 --> 00:15:20,662
Close your eyes.

170
00:15:21,830 --> 00:15:23,206
- What for?
- Come on.

171
00:15:23,790 --> 00:15:26,418
I won't do anything weird.
Relax and close your eyes.

172
00:15:30,588 --> 00:15:31,589
Okay.

173
00:15:32,882 --> 00:15:34,175
What do you hear?

174
00:15:35,552 --> 00:15:37,011
I hear the rain. What else?

175
00:15:37,095 --> 00:15:40,181
Calm yourself and focus
on the sounds around you.

176
00:15:54,112 --> 00:15:56,990
The sound of raindrops
hitting the windows.

177
00:15:57,907 --> 00:15:58,992
And?

178
00:15:59,868 --> 00:16:00,994
"And"?

179
00:16:02,328 --> 00:16:04,330
- The car's engine.
- And?

180
00:16:08,001 --> 00:16:09,669
A passing motorcycle.

181
00:16:11,421 --> 00:16:12,464
What else?

182
00:16:17,510 --> 00:16:18,595
Kids laughing

183
00:16:19,554 --> 00:16:20,722
in the distance.

184
00:16:22,056 --> 00:16:23,099
And?

185
00:16:26,436 --> 00:16:27,729
The sound of your breath.

186
00:16:28,646 --> 00:16:29,689
And?

187
00:16:35,361 --> 00:16:36,571
My heartbeat.

188
00:16:42,452 --> 00:16:44,037
That's how you feel it.

189
00:16:47,081 --> 00:16:50,335
If you look within yourself
just hard enough

190
00:16:51,169 --> 00:16:52,629
with all your heart

191
00:16:55,006 --> 00:16:56,299
happiness is right there.

192
00:16:58,051 --> 00:16:59,594
It's always there

193
00:17:00,428 --> 00:17:01,638
so whenever you want to find it

194
00:17:04,098 --> 00:17:05,308
do what you did just now.

195
00:17:37,423 --> 00:17:38,967
Welcome back!

196
00:17:39,676 --> 00:17:41,511
- Glad you're okay.
- Thank you.

197
00:17:42,804 --> 00:17:44,639
You had a tough time, Mr. Noh.

198
00:17:45,056 --> 00:17:46,432
But you look

199
00:17:47,016 --> 00:17:48,393
even better than before.

200
00:17:48,476 --> 00:17:49,811
Did the hospital food
suit your taste?

201
00:17:50,645 --> 00:17:53,106
He looks better
because he was away from work.

202
00:17:53,189 --> 00:17:54,899
Don't be silly.

203
00:17:54,983 --> 00:17:57,402
Mr. Noh always looked good.

204
00:17:57,485 --> 00:18:00,029
The office is brighter
now that you're back.

205
00:18:00,113 --> 00:18:01,197
Welcome back.

206
00:18:01,489 --> 00:18:04,784
I missed you so very much, Mr. Noh.

207
00:18:05,410 --> 00:18:06,953
Don't go overboard.

208
00:18:07,537 --> 00:18:09,622
You don't have to worry
about Mr. Ahn.

209
00:18:09,706 --> 00:18:13,918
Legal is taking an aggressive stance.
He'll pay a hefty price.

210
00:18:14,002 --> 00:18:16,212
It looks like his family
cut ties with him, too.

211
00:18:16,296 --> 00:18:18,256
He brought it upon himself.
You did well, Mr. Noh.

212
00:18:18,840 --> 00:18:19,882
Thanks.

213
00:18:19,966 --> 00:18:21,968
Your teammates must love you.

214
00:18:22,051 --> 00:18:24,012
You didn't want to transfer
in the beginning, though.

215
00:18:24,429 --> 00:18:27,307
- You wanted to transfer.
- Yes, more than anything.

216
00:18:27,390 --> 00:18:29,017
Yes, that's true.

217
00:18:29,559 --> 00:18:31,060
Good morning, Ms. Joo.

218
00:18:32,228 --> 00:18:33,771
- Hello.
- Morning.

219
00:18:33,980 --> 00:18:35,398
You're back, Mr. Noh.

220
00:18:35,773 --> 00:18:37,442
Yes, I'm back, Ms. Joo.

221
00:18:37,525 --> 00:18:40,069
Ms. Joo.
Do you have special plans for later?

222
00:18:40,153 --> 00:18:42,655
You look nicer than usual.
I almost didn't recognize you.

223
00:18:46,743 --> 00:18:49,370
Are you saying I looked dowdy before?

224
00:18:49,871 --> 00:18:52,123
No, that's not what I meant.

225
00:18:52,206 --> 00:18:54,167
You must be in a good mood
for some reason.

226
00:18:54,250 --> 00:18:56,169
Could it be the return
of your favorite employee?

227
00:18:56,753 --> 00:18:58,963
- I don't expect a lavish welcome...
- Mr. Noh.

228
00:19:01,716 --> 00:19:05,053
You lost touch with how things are
while you were away.

229
00:19:09,682 --> 00:19:11,684
I should help you return to reality.

230
00:19:18,816 --> 00:19:21,736
I guess Ms. Joo still dislikes you.

231
00:19:22,487 --> 00:19:24,447
I think the stabbing
didn't really change anything.

232
00:19:28,701 --> 00:19:29,786
It's fine.

233
00:19:30,119 --> 00:19:31,412
This is nothing.

234
00:19:32,080 --> 00:19:33,873
I'm Noh Ki-jun,
the ace of the Audit Team.

235
00:19:35,249 --> 00:19:36,376
Thanks.

236
00:19:36,959 --> 00:19:38,503
Okay, let's do this.

237
00:20:03,778 --> 00:20:06,614
I finished all the tasks you gave me.

238
00:20:07,740 --> 00:20:09,117
AUDIT TEAM HEAD JOO IN-A

239
00:20:09,200 --> 00:20:10,368
OK

240
00:20:11,577 --> 00:20:13,121
"OK"?

241
00:20:17,583 --> 00:20:19,293
This is too much.

242
00:20:23,256 --> 00:20:25,883
This is too much.
My first day after a stabbing...

243
00:20:29,804 --> 00:20:31,556
You worked hard today.
I'll treat you to a meal.

244
00:20:32,390 --> 00:20:34,225
You will? When?

245
00:20:35,101 --> 00:20:41,899
AUDIT TEAM HEAD JOO IN-A

246
00:20:50,074 --> 00:20:52,368
Friday evening. Come to my place.

247
00:20:58,666 --> 00:20:59,834
What's the matter?

248
00:21:03,045 --> 00:21:05,089
- It's my back.
- Is your back sore?

249
00:21:28,196 --> 00:21:29,322
Mr. Noh.

250
00:21:29,989 --> 00:21:31,449
Hey, Doo-gi.

251
00:21:31,991 --> 00:21:34,452
I'm sorry I couldn't visit you
in the hospital.

252
00:21:35,620 --> 00:21:36,746
Don't be.

253
00:21:37,413 --> 00:21:40,208
I won't visit you in the hospital
if you ever get stabbed.

254
00:21:40,291 --> 00:21:41,375
We're even.

255
00:21:42,376 --> 00:21:43,586
Fine, whatever.

256
00:21:45,546 --> 00:21:49,050
Oh, right.
I have a work-related question.

257
00:21:49,133 --> 00:21:51,969
- Yes?
- You handled Haemu Pharmaceutical.

258
00:21:52,345 --> 00:21:53,429
Yes, I did.

259
00:21:53,513 --> 00:21:56,015
Were you working
on anything in particular?

260
00:21:56,724 --> 00:21:58,351
What are you talking about?

261
00:21:58,684 --> 00:22:01,145
