512
00:44:32,571 --> 00:44:35,282
Anyway, what did you two talk about
in the interview room?

513
00:44:40,120 --> 00:44:43,582
Wait, we're here to celebrate him.
Why has he been downing drinks

514
00:44:43,665 --> 00:44:45,417
with that frown on his face?

515
00:44:45,500 --> 00:44:47,294
Tell me about it.
It's a great occasion.

516
00:44:48,670 --> 00:44:52,215
Wait, is it because
you don't want to buy us a drink?

517
00:44:52,299 --> 00:44:53,425
Hey, no way.

518
00:44:57,095 --> 00:44:58,221
Excellent.

519
00:44:58,471 --> 00:45:00,807
I think you should come along

520
00:45:01,558 --> 00:45:03,059
to the Jeju business trip, Ms. Joo.

521
00:45:04,644 --> 00:45:05,729
Me?

522
00:45:06,980 --> 00:45:08,607
What's there
for the Audit Team to do?

523
00:45:08,690 --> 00:45:11,026
You were with CPK and JV
while you worked abroad.

524
00:45:11,109 --> 00:45:14,529
You'll help break the ice
as an experienced partner.

525
00:45:15,196 --> 00:45:18,158
In that case, Ms. Joo must go.

526
00:45:19,075 --> 00:45:20,702
Gosh, I'm jealous.

527
00:45:21,745 --> 00:45:23,705
Jeju must be nice around this time.

528
00:45:44,351 --> 00:45:45,894
It's my birthday.

529
00:45:49,147 --> 00:45:50,565
So why don't I grab a drink?

530
00:46:18,343 --> 00:46:20,553
JEON JAE-YEOL
DESTINATION: JEJU

531
00:46:34,067 --> 00:46:36,444
Hi. Let's have a drink.
It's been a while.

532
00:46:54,754 --> 00:46:56,381
You heard me at the meeting, right?

533
00:46:56,881 --> 00:46:58,383
Get me ready
for the business trip next week.

534
00:46:58,466 --> 00:47:00,051
Why Ms. Joo In-a?

535
00:47:00,969 --> 00:47:03,471
There are more than enough reasons
for Ms. Joo In-a to accompany me.

536
00:47:03,555 --> 00:47:05,473
She's an experienced partner
who knows the other party.

537
00:47:05,557 --> 00:47:07,267
Not that, but the real reason.

538
00:47:09,144 --> 00:47:10,770
What do you think you're doing?

539
00:47:10,854 --> 00:47:13,273
No, what do you think you're doing?

540
00:47:13,356 --> 00:47:14,774
Not only do you get
into a drunken fight

541
00:47:14,858 --> 00:47:17,277
but you're sending an employee
overseas because of your feelings.

542
00:47:17,736 --> 00:47:20,280
Do you know
what people are saying about you?

543
00:47:20,363 --> 00:47:22,073
That the managing director
will become the president

544
00:47:22,157 --> 00:47:23,742
and you'll be kicked out.

545
00:47:24,200 --> 00:47:27,162
"Will he leave without causing a mess
or lose everything miserably?"

546
00:47:27,245 --> 00:47:29,122
They're saying
those two are the only options.

547
00:47:29,581 --> 00:47:31,207
In times like these

548
00:47:32,208 --> 00:47:35,378
why do you keep making mistakes
because of uncontained emotions?

549
00:47:36,212 --> 00:47:38,006
I'm used to hearing
people talk like that.

550
00:47:38,840 --> 00:47:40,008
And I regret

551
00:47:40,717 --> 00:47:42,010
letting those have an effect

552
00:47:42,761 --> 00:47:44,637
on acting true to my emotions.

553
00:47:47,599 --> 00:47:48,850
So what now?

554
00:47:48,933 --> 00:47:50,393
What can you do
by being true to your emotions?

555
00:47:50,477 --> 00:47:52,395
Are you going to die with Joo In-a?

556
00:47:52,479 --> 00:47:54,314
You said she was a woman
you could die with.

557
00:47:54,898 --> 00:47:57,817
Ms. Park A-jeong, you seem to be
the one who's emotional, not me.

558
00:47:57,901 --> 00:47:58,985
So?

559
00:47:59,819 --> 00:48:01,905
Can you even give up everything
for that woman?

560
00:48:02,906 --> 00:48:04,074
If I must.

561
00:48:26,179 --> 00:48:27,722
What are these?

562
00:48:34,395 --> 00:48:36,356
Why did I get this?
I never even use it.

563
00:48:37,774 --> 00:48:41,319
From now on, I swear
to live as a minimalist.

564
00:48:45,198 --> 00:48:46,616
Hey, just leave those.

565
00:48:46,991 --> 00:48:49,661
I'm sure there are dishes in the US.
You can use them.

566
00:48:50,954 --> 00:48:54,582
Anyway, come to think of it,
I'm glad you moved in here.

567
00:48:55,041 --> 00:48:58,545
It would've been too much work
to rent out the place while I'm gone.

568
00:49:02,132 --> 00:49:04,092
Hey, are you listening?

569
00:49:04,843 --> 00:49:06,094
Ki-jun.

570
00:49:06,594 --> 00:49:08,513
Do you know that
the vice president and Joo In-a

571
00:49:09,305 --> 00:49:11,307
are going to Jeju next week?

572
00:49:13,643 --> 00:49:16,229
I do. I saw the schedule.

573
00:49:17,188 --> 00:49:20,817
They've traveled there together.

574
00:49:21,568 --> 00:49:23,945
It must be such a dear memory.

575
00:49:24,195 --> 00:49:26,364
He even kept the old plane ticket.

576
00:49:29,492 --> 00:49:31,035
Sounds humble.

577
00:49:31,661 --> 00:49:34,038
I didn't know even rich people
like him go to Jeju as a couple.

578
00:49:37,792 --> 00:49:40,170
Hey, I said you can use that cup.

579
00:49:41,754 --> 00:49:43,214
Did you pack all these?

580
00:49:44,132 --> 00:49:46,634
Just leave these dishes
back in the cupboard.

581
00:49:53,766 --> 00:49:55,018
Are you okay?

582
00:50:01,024 --> 00:50:03,276
I'll get it. That must be our food.

583
00:50:21,461 --> 00:50:22,545
Ki-jun.

584
00:50:46,419 --> 00:50:49,256
I'll step out for a moment.
We're out of drinking water.

585
00:50:49,339 --> 00:50:51,049
- Okay. Sure.
- Excuse me.

586
00:50:59,808 --> 00:51:02,018
What? Why? Did I do anything wrong?

587
00:51:02,102 --> 00:51:04,521
I just explained everything.
She's renting out a room from me.

588
00:51:06,731 --> 00:51:08,233
Stop pinching me, will you?

589
00:51:09,860 --> 00:51:12,654
Hey, what is wrong with you?

590
00:51:12,737 --> 00:51:14,406
You kept a woman
by your side at the hospital

591
00:51:14,489 --> 00:51:15,949
but actually live with another?

592
00:51:16,032 --> 00:51:17,325
Who do you think you are?

593
00:51:17,409 --> 00:51:20,370
I'm a nobody. Okay?
But you know what?

594
00:51:22,664 --> 00:51:23,874
That woman isn't into me.

595
00:51:25,041 --> 00:51:27,043
What kind of nonsense is this?

596
00:51:27,127 --> 00:51:30,005
Hey. How could she do that
if she wasn't into you?

597
00:51:31,506 --> 00:51:33,967
I don't know, but she said
she likes another man.

598
00:51:34,050 --> 00:51:35,260
So you forget about her, too.

599
00:51:37,929 --> 00:51:40,390
You foolish idiot!

600
00:51:40,473 --> 00:51:43,101
You can't just take her words
and take it as is.

601
00:51:43,184 --> 00:51:46,229
Pay attention to her demeanor,
actions, and look in her eyes!

602
00:51:46,313 --> 00:51:49,983
Think of the way she looked at you
while you were at the hospital.

603
00:51:50,066 --> 00:51:53,236
Good grief. You're so slow.

604
00:53:46,057 --> 00:53:49,185
Oddly enough, I have a habit

605
00:53:50,395 --> 00:53:52,480
of hiding the truth
when it matters most.

606
00:54:15,670 --> 00:54:18,089
- Hey.
- Where are they staying in Jeju?

607
00:54:18,673 --> 00:54:20,800
- What?
- Where's Joo In-a staying in Jeju?

608
00:54:21,384 --> 00:54:24,054
Why? Are you going to go after her?

609
00:54:24,137 --> 00:54:25,722
I'm asking you! Where is she?

610
00:54:28,475 --> 00:54:30,018
Jeon Jae-yeol, Noh Ki-jun.

611
00:54:32,103 --> 00:54:33,646
You're both insane.

612
00:54:48,203 --> 00:54:51,289
The terms don't look so bad
though you'll need to verify.

613
00:54:52,165 --> 00:54:54,417
I'd prefer the investment
to be bigger.

614
00:54:55,251 --> 00:54:57,128
But a higher risk
will come with that.

615
00:54:57,212 --> 00:54:59,255
CPK is just a money-lending business.

616
00:54:59,339 --> 00:55:00,381
There's no soul.

617
00:55:07,972 --> 00:55:09,182
It's nice to be here with you.

618
00:55:13,937 --> 00:55:15,146
Jeju, I mean.

619
00:55:16,523 --> 00:55:19,734
It was our first and last trip.

620
00:55:21,486 --> 00:55:24,322
We managed to take a leave
at the same time and come here

621
00:55:25,490 --> 00:55:27,534
but only worked the whole time
just like we're doing now.

622
00:55:31,955 --> 00:55:34,082
The biggest concern now
is the formation of the board.

623
00:55:34,165 --> 00:55:35,166
In-a.

624
00:55:40,588 --> 00:55:42,841
Mr. Vice President, it seems like
you're having a hard time focusing.

625
00:55:43,967 --> 00:55:46,469
I'll look over this separately
and report back to you.

626
00:55:46,553 --> 00:55:47,887
Wait, In-a.

627
00:55:49,848 --> 00:55:51,099
Can we sit here...

628
00:55:53,101 --> 00:55:54,853
like the old days for a moment?

629
00:56:02,026 --> 00:56:03,444
That's not going to happen.

630
00:56:05,155 --> 00:56:06,781
We can't go back
to how things used to be.

631
00:56:07,448 --> 00:56:09,242
Then why did you return to Korea?

632
00:56:20,712 --> 00:56:21,754
To honor what I said.

633
00:56:23,506 --> 00:56:25,592
I promised to take your side.

634
00:56:26,968 --> 00:56:28,595
So this is the last I can do
to honor my words.

635
00:56:28,678 --> 00:56:29,929
That's more than enough.

636
00:56:30,013 --> 00:56:32,473
I don't care how you feel
and why you're doing it.

637
00:56:34,142 --> 00:56:35,685
Please just stay by my side.

638
00:56:37,103 --> 00:56:38,271
That's all I need.

639
00:56:45,528 --> 00:56:46,988
I'm done doing that, too.

640
00:56:48,781 --> 00:56:50,366
I got caught up with that promise

641
00:56:52,952 --> 00:56:54,704
and made a mistake I shouldn't have.

642
00:56:57,707 --> 00:56:59,417
And I hurt someone.

643
00:57:02,253 --> 00:57:03,838
I shouldn't have done that to him.

644
00:57:08,092 --> 00:57:09,677
Are you talking about Mr. Noh Ki-jun?

645
00:57:21,981 --> 00:57:23,316
What I'm trying to say is

646
00:57:24,859 --> 00:57:27,028
I'm never going back to you,
Jae-yeol.

647
00:58:53,573 --> 00:58:55,199
It must be far too late

648
00:58:56,492 --> 00:58:57,702
to go to you.

649
00:59:04,584 --> 00:59:05,752
Joo In-a!

650
00:59:29,692 --> 00:59:30,943
Joo In-a!

651
00:59:48,419 --> 00:59:49,545
Noh Ki-jun.

652
01:00:05,478 --> 01:00:07,814
Why did you check out already?

653
01:00:09,065 --> 01:00:10,983
I had to go all the way to the hotel.

654
01:01:56,172 --> 01:01:58,591
HAEMU STRATEGIC PLANNING, MARKETING,
DIGITAL MARKETING, AUDIT TEAM 1, 2, 3

655
01:02:04,138 --> 01:02:06,140
...IS INVOLVED IN AN INAPPROPRIATE
WORKPLACE RELATIONSHIP

656
01:02:08,059 --> 01:02:10,353
MS. JOO IN-A...

657
01:02:17,860 --> 01:02:19,237
SEND, HIDE SENDER

658
01:02:19,320 --> 01:02:22,865
SEND

659
01:02:22,949 --> 01:02:25,868
FILING FOR LOVE

660
01:02:54,230 --> 01:02:56,023
I'm kind of worried

661
01:02:56,107 --> 01:02:58,568
that I won't be able to hide
how much I like you at work.

662
01:03:00,278 --> 01:03:01,779
Clear your schedule this weekend.

663
01:03:01,862 --> 01:03:03,447
I booked a pool villa in Sokcho.

664
01:03:03,531 --> 01:03:05,157
Mr. Noh, you should go
to Mr. Min's club

665
01:03:05,241 --> 01:03:06,784
- this weekend.
- What?

666
01:03:06,867 --> 01:03:08,828
You said you get passionate
when you start dating.

667
01:03:08,911 --> 01:03:10,329
But all you did was
make me work passionately.

668
01:03:10,413 --> 01:03:12,623
Mr. Noh, do you want to stay
for ramyeon?

669
01:03:13,499 --> 01:03:16,419
You must be enjoying yourself
caught between two men.

670
01:03:16,502 --> 01:03:17,712
I'm getting a divorce.

671
01:03:17,795 --> 01:03:19,338
I regret everything, In-a.

672
01:03:19,672 --> 01:03:20,965
What's going on?

673
01:03:34,353 --> 01:03:36,355
Subtitles by Eunsook Youn
and Jennifer Lim
